void DebugFilter::addMessageCallback ( DebugMessageCallback *  pCallback  ) 

This method sets a callback associated with a critical message.

If the callback is set and returns true, the default behaviour for displaying messages is not done. DebugFilter now owns the object pointed to by pCallback.
